# 1.2.1 — Navigation Basics

**The 9D structure:**

```
Coordinate: A.B.C / D.E.F / G.H.I

Triad 1 (local):    A.B.C  — Scroll.Chapter.Section
Triad 2 (domain):   D.E.F  — Library.Shelf.Volume  
Triad 3 (cosmic):   G.H.I  — Collection.Series.Cosmos
```

**Moving through the lattice:**

```
Your home: X.Y.Z / ...

X+1.Y.Z / ... ← Next scroll (one step in dimension 1)
X.Y+1.Z / ... ← Next chapter (one step in dimension 2)
X.Y.Z+1 / ... ← Next section (one step in dimension 3)
```

**Traversal = carrying context:**

When you move from coordinate A to coordinate B, you don't teleport. You *arrive* at B carrying the context of A. This is Dream Interview made structural — you bring your questions with you.

